  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>This hotel is offered on a bed and breakfast or half board basis.</p>
<p>Fuel up for a day on the mountain with the continental breakfast buffet with additional hot options offered each day served at the Restaurant L'Aiguille Percee.</p>
<p>If you on a half board basis you will also enjoy dinner in the Restaurant L'Aiguille Percee, or as part of the half-board option, you can enjoy dinner in the other restaurants in the hotel collection that are all located nearby. These include Il Savoia (with supplement), Les Terrasses Du Levanna, Le Chalet and La Brasserie De L'arbina. These restaurants pride themselves on using local, seasonal produce which is used to create authentic and tasty menus. There are also a number of restaurants close by serving traditional Savoyard cuisine including the regions favourite dish, fondue.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel l'Aiguille Percee is a great addition to our programme in <a data-udi="umb://document/204ce8e4cf8c4ab09205501e16cb7565" href="/{localLink:umb://document/204ce8e4cf8c4ab09205501e16cb7565}" title="Tignes">Tignes</a>, offering quick and easy access to one of the best ski resorts in the world, <a data-udi="umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03}" title="Tignes-Val d’Isere Ski Area">Tignes- Val d'Isere Ski Area</a>, from a stylish hotel with great wellness facilities. </p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>You have excellent access to the Tignes-Val d'Isere ski area from the main ski lifts, which are just a short walk away from the Hotel l'Aiguille Percee. The wonderful <a data-udi="umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03}" title="Tignes-Val d’Isere Ski Area">Tignes- Val d'Isere</a> has over 300km of slopes with a variety of slopes for all levels of skier or boarder. After a day on the slopes, make the most of the bars, restaurants and shops which are all close by to the hotel. </p>
<h2>Cosy accommodation</h2>
<p>The hotel is built in the typical Alpine style and features a combination of stone and wood throughout its interior. The rooms have a more contemporary feel to them, with modern furnishings inspired by the surroundings. Each room has all of the amenities needed for a week in the mountains, relax with a bit of TV or take in the breath-taking views of the resort and surrounding Alpine peaks.</p>
<h2>Relax and unwind</h2>
<p>After a long day on the slopes, come back to the hotel and relax in the wellness area. Soak away the aches and pains in the heated indoor pool or unwind in the hammam, or sauna. </p>
<p>Unwind for the evening in the cosy restaurant which serve a variety of dishes inspired by the Alps where modern flavours compliment traditional dishes. The hotel also offers you the choice of dining in other Etincelles Collection restaurants for an additional supplement. The restaurants the l'Aiguille Percee work with all pride themselves on using fresh and local produce to create delicious menus which offer both regional and international dishes.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
