  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Comfort rooms</strong> sleep two people and have a double bed. The rooms have a private ensuite with a shower room or a bath.</p>
<p><strong>Privilege double rooms</strong> sleep two people and have twin beds. Most privilege rooms have a balcony overlooking the resort and slopes. The rooms have a shower.  These rooms can accommodate a cot. </p>
<p><strong>Privilege triple rooms</strong> sleep three people and have three single beds, however can be made into a double bed and one single on request. These rooms have a bath.  These rooms can accommodate a cot. </p>
<p><strong>Bedroom facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Most rooms can be made up as either twin or double beds (please specify when booking)</li>
<li>Ensuite bathroom with a shower or bath</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Hair dryer </li>
<li>Welcome amenities</li>
<li>Daily housekeeping</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
